Key Match Events: Rudy Gobert made a driving layup against Wembanyama that was initially whistled for an offensive foul. Timberwolves coach Chris Finch challenged the call, and the basket was allowed to stand. Minnesota didn't trail the rest of the way.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Anthony Edwards, who earlier in the day was fined $100,000 for continued use of profanity in postgame comments, was held to 14 points, 11 below his season average.
Others: The Spurs found a wide-open Jeremy Sochan for a potential game-winning three-pointer, but he came up short.
